  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Genjutsu (Phantasm)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 2 (Spell Level 1)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 3</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 14 | <b>Successes:</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 2 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 13</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You can make minor, illusory modifications within the area to trick or deceive others. You may make up to one minor change per level. The technique can only affected unattended objects or create the illusion of such objects. A minor change is a small detail, such as the inscription on a door or plaque, making a Small sized object appear or disappear, etc. Such a change cannot directly cause harm.<br><br>A creature interacting with an object created by the technique will immediately notice that something is not quite right, and can only make a save to disbelief after it has identified or studied the illusion.<br><br>This technique can be dispelled, which renders the affected creature immune to that instance of the technique.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
